  ],
  "text": "Five files under pkg/components/loki/ implement Loki client retry and timeout logic:\n\n1. pkg/components/loki/lokihttp/client.go — The HTTP Loki client implementation. It defines the `client` struct and the `StopNow()` method (line ~376), which cancels the context to stop retrying HTTP requests immediately. It also uses `BackoffConfig` to create a backoff loop (`backoff.New(c.ctx, c.cfg.BackoffConfig)` around line 299) that retries failed sends. The `Client` interface (around line 120) declares both `Stop()` and `StopNow()`.\n\n2. pkg/components/loki/lokihttp/config.go — The HTTP client configuration struct. It defines `BackoffConfig backoff.Config` and `Timeout time.Duration` fields (around lines 19–20), which drive the retry/backoff and per-request timeout behaviour of the HTTP Loki client.\n\n3. pkg/components/loki/lokihttp/fake.go — A fake/stub HTTP Loki client used in tests. It implements the `Client` interface including a no-op `StopNow()` method (line ~39), satisfying the interface contract for unit testing.\n\n4. pkg/components/loki/lokigrpc/client.go — The gRPC Loki client implementation. It configures retry behaviour via `grpcretry.WithMax(c.cfg.Retries)` (line ~85) using the grpc_retry interceptor. It also implements `timeoutCtx()` (line ~90) which uses `context.WithTimeout` based on `c.cfg.Timeout` to enforce per-call deadlines.\n\n5. pkg/components/loki/lokigrpc/config.go — The gRPC client configuration struct. It defines `Retries uint` and `Timeout time.Duration` fields (lines ~9–10), which control the maximum number of gRPC retries (consumed by `grpcretry.WithMax`) and the per-call timeout."
}

